5. RANDOMNESS & FAIRNESS AUDIT
‚ö†Ô∏è CRITICAL CONCERN: Unverifiable Randomness
Observations:

"Provably Fair" Button Present - The UI includes a "Provably Fair Information" button, but its implementation could not be audited without triggering transactions
Game Mechanics - The platform appears to be a multiplier-based game where:

Users BUY/SELL positions
Multipliers increase over time
Game "crashes" at unpredictable points
"Golden Hour" events with prize drawings


Randomness Source: Unknown

Cannot verify if randomness is:

Generated on-chain (VRF program)
Generated server-side (centralized)
Deterministically reproducible
Known before user commitment





üö© RED FLAGS for Fairness

Custodial model = platform controls fund flow
Client-side JavaScript = game logic potentially manipulable
No observable on-chain settlement = results could be determined off-chain
Privy integration = transactions may be pre-approved without user explicit signing

Trust Dependencies
Users must trust:

Rugs.fun backend for fair randomness
Privy for secure wallet management
Platform custodianship of deposited funds
Correctness of "Provably Fair" implementation (if any)


