Backend (Inferred):
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Game state server
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Custodial wallet system
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Telemetry ingestion
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Socket.IO real-time services
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Privy policy/approval APIs
Transaction Flow (Theoretical)
1. User connects Phantom via Privy
2. User deposits SOL ‚Üí Platform custody
3. Game bets use internal balance (off-chain ledger)
4. Game results computed (server-side?)
5. Balance updated in platform database
6. User withdraws ‚Üí On-chain Solana transaction

7. TRUST MODEL ANALYSIS
Centralization Points

Privy MPC Wallets - Third-party custody layer
Internal Balance System - Platform holds user funds
Game Logic Server - Outcome determination
Randomness Generation - Source unverified

On-Chain vs Off-Chain

DEPOSIT/WITHDRAW: On-chain Solana transactions
GAME PLAY: Appears to be off-chain (custodial balance manipulation)
SETTLEMENT: Likely off-chain database updates

Conclusion: This is NOT a fully on-chain game. It is a hybrid custodial platform with on-chain entry/exit points but off-chain gameplay.

8. RED FLAGS & SECURITY CONCERNS
üî¥ Critical Issues

Custodial Risk - Users lose custody of funds during gameplay
Unverified Fairness - Cannot independently audit randomness or game outcomes
Privy Dependency - Third-party controls wallet signing flow
Extensive Telemetry - User behavior tracking and fingerprinting
Opaque Settlement - Game results not observable on-chain

‚ö†Ô∏è Moderate Concerns

WebSocket Communication - Game state updates via Socket.IO (encrypted but opaque)
Client-Side Transaction Building - Potential for manipulation or bugs
No Rate Limiting Observable - Deposit/withdrawal protections unclear
WalletConnect Integration - Additional attack surface

‚ÑπÔ∏è Informational

Chat System - Real-time user communication (potential for social engineering)
Leaderboard System - PnL tracking (privacy implications)
Level/XP System - Gamification encouraging continued play


9. SAMPLE TRANSACTION ANALYSIS
‚ö†Ô∏è Unable to Capture Live Transactions
Reason: The platform requires funds in custody (0.000 SOL balance) to trigger actual blockchain transactions. During the audit period:

DEPOSIT button was non-responsive or requires additional authentication
BUY/SELL buttons do not trigger transactions with zero balance
No wallet signature prompts were generated

Transaction Hooks Installed:

window.solana.signTransaction - Hooked ‚úÖ
window.solana.signAndSendTransaction - Hooked ‚úÖ
No transactions captured during audit window


10. RECOMMENDATIONS
For Users:

Understand the trust model - You are trusting Rugs.fun and Privy with custody
Verify "Provably Fair" - Check if the fairness mechanism is actually auditable
Limit deposits - Only deposit what you can afford to lose
Review Privy permissions - Understand what transaction authority you've granted
Monitor withdrawals - Ensure you can actually withdraw funds

For the Platform:

Publish program IDs - Make Solana programs open-source for auditing
Implement on-chain settlement - Move game logic to Solana programs
Use verifiable VRF - Integrate Switchboard/Pyth for provable randomness
Minimize custodial holdings - Allow users to play directly from wallets
Transparency - Document the trust model clearly for users

For Auditors:

Fund test account - Deposit SOL to capture actual transactions
Monitor RPC calls - Use network inspection to capture Solana JSON-RPC
Decompile programs - If program IDs are found, analyze bytecode
Test withdrawal flow - Verify users can actually exit with funds


11. CONCLUSIONS
Game Classification: Hybrid Custodial
Rugs.fun is not a fully on-chain Solana game. It implements a custodial balance system where:

Entry/exit points use Solana blockchain
Gameplay and settlement appear to be off-chain
Users must trust the platform for fair outcomes

Privy/MPC Trust Model Impact
Privy adds a layer of abstraction that:

‚úÖ Simplifies wallet onboarding
‚úÖ Enables social login integration
‚ùå Introduces third-party custody risk
‚ùå May enable transaction pre-approval without explicit signing
‚ùå Creates additional centralization

Fairness: Unverifiable
Without capturing actual transactions and analyzing on-chain state, game fairness cannot be independently verified. The "Provably Fair" claim requires deeper investigation.
Overall Assessment
‚ö†Ô∏è MEDIUM-HIGH RISK - The platform's custodial model and opaque game mechanics create significant trust dependencies. Users should be aware they are effectively playing on a centralized platform with blockchain entry/exit points, not a fully decentralized on-chain game.

